  {
    "id": "UgxqnTGf5xKpSnh-6514AaABAg",
    "author": "@3dw3dw",
    "author_channel_id": "UCIOljMMd9XjeuLM9GqmD-zA",
    "text": "There are no brass gears in your transmission.  Those brass things are synchronizer rings. They do not carry a load as a gear does. The help to align the splines of the selector hub to the gear spline.\nThose synchronizers are what allows gear changes on the fly.\nWithout the synchronizer one would have to completely stop in order to change from one gear to the other or be ridiculously good at rev matching.",
    "likes": 1,
    "published_at": "2021-08-20T04:21:17Z",
    "reply_count": 1,
    "replies": [
      {
        "id": "UgxqnTGf5xKpSnh-6514AaABAg.9RFaRZyyMN_9RFkk1mh3ZU",
